artists.name: Taylor Swift
blurbs: Taylor Swift is a clever country starlet with a honeyed voice who started writing songs when she was 10.
Swift recorded her self-titled debut album when she was just 16. Remarkably, she wrote all 12 songs.
She was brought up in a musical family. Her grandmother was a professional opera singer and had Taylor singing as a child.
At the young age of 12, Taylor picked up a guitar and taught herself to play. She used to fret chords until her fingers bled.
Although Taylor Swift's musical career blossomed smack dab in the middle of high school, she maintained a straight 4.0 G.P.A.

bios.title: Nate Cavalieri
bios.author: Nate Cavalieri
bios.bio: With her homespun charm, curly golden locks, and prodigious gift for songwriting, Taylor Swift is one of the youngest Nashville newcomers to capture a national audience in years. When she was just 16, Swift's first big single, "Tim McGraw," peaked at No. 3 on the Billboard country chart and held a spot in the top 10 for months. On the single's success, Swift joined the ranks of teenage country queens like Tanya Tucker, Marie Osmond and LeAnn Rimes, who all charted as teenagers. Unlike those young chart-toppers, Swift wrote the song herself. Born in Wyomissing, Penn., in 1989, Swift began playing guitar at 12, and moved outside of Nashville with her family as a teen, and debuted at the Bluebird Cafe famed songwriter showcase. Her self-titled debut album, issued in October 2006, spawned a handful of radio hits such as "Tim McGraw," "Our Song" and "Picture to Burn," all of which propelled Taylor Swift to triple-platinum status. Not bad for a beginner! Preceded by the hit "Love Story," Swift's sophomore effort, Fearless, was released in November 2008.

artists.name: Drake
blurbs: Aubrey Drake Graham is a biracial, half-Canadian, half-American artist that blends hip-hop street smarts and lush emo R&B.
Drake played basketball player Jimmy Brooks on Canadian TV's Degrassi: The Next Generation in the early '00s.
Drake's Memphis-based African-American father, Dennis Graham, used to drum for Jerry Lee Lewis.
Drake's uncle, rhythm guitarist Mabon "Teene" Hodges, wrote a number of hits for Al Green.
Drake's first two albums debuted at number one on the charts.

bios.title: Bebop Digital
bios.author: Bebop Digital
bios.bio: Cantor e rapper canadense, Drake começou sua carreira artística como ator. A vontade de triunfar na música o fez abandonar a série Degrassi: The Next Generation, que o tornou conhecido no Canadá no começo dos anos 2000. Seus primeiros lançamentos como músico foram mixtapes independentes. Em pouco tempo, Drake chamou a atenção do rapper Lil Wayne, que o trouxe para a sua gravadora, a Young Money. Thank Me Later, seu primeiro álbum, chegou em 2010, emplacando os hits “Find Your Love” e “Over”. No ano seguinte, Drake veio com Take Care, que ampliou seu sucesso. Nada menos do que oito singles do trabalho chegaram às paradas, incluindo “The Motto” e “Headlines”. Com Nothing Was the Same (2013), o MC entrou em quase todas as listas de melhores registros daquele ano e emplacou os hits “Started from the Bottom” e “Pound Cake” entre outros. Em 2015, com o megahit “Hotline Bling”, Drake se tornou conhecido mundialmente. “One Dance” e “Too Good”, singles do álbum Views, mantiveram seu nome em alta em 2016.

artists.name: The-Dream
blurbs: R&B singer/songwriter The-Dream shot up the charts in late 2007 with his ubiquitous debut single, "Shawty Is da Sh*t (10)."
The-Dream is the writer of such hits as Rihanna's "Umbrella" and J Holiday's "Bed."
The-Dream claims that he wrote "Umbrella" in 12 minutes.
The-Dream's solo debut, Love Hate, dropped in December of 2007.
While critics love The-Dream, his solo success pales next to the hits he's written for Beyonce, Jamie Foxx and others.

bios.title: Sam Chennault
bios.author: Sam Chennault
bios.bio: Atlanta singer-songwriter The-Dream (born Terius Nash) became a household name in late 2007 with his smash hit "Shawty Is a 10." With a drooping melody, light synth embellishments and a piano line that dances around the downbeat, the song -- off his December 2007 debut, Lovehate -- is the equivalent of R&B cotton candy. But Nash's story begins before then. Among many other credits, he wrote Rihanna's smash hit "Umbrella," as well as J. Holiday's "Bed." In addition to "Shawty Is a 10," The-Dream also scored big with Lovehate's "Falsetto" and "I Luv Your Girl." In 2009, he released sophomore effort Love Vs Money. The album channels the lite electro-funk of Prince, while also echoing R. Kelly's arrogant sexuality. Add The-Dream's uncanny ear for melody and ability to sculpt instantly memorable hooks, and you have one of the biggest new stars in R&B.
